= Task 1
== Problem Setup
=== Initial problem
A robot must move from a given start position to a given goal position in a 2D environment while avoiding obstacles and producing a smooth trajectory.

Since the trajectory is defined as
$ {x_1,x_2,dots,x_n} in RR^2. $

Lets fix 2 points, that is the starting point $x_1$ and the goal point $x_n$

$ x_1 = vec(1,1), quad x_n = vec(100,100). $

For this one can define a class in python to handle the search space. This way, whenever any a good path $x in RR^2 $ is found, the search space trajectory is updated.

=== Straight path
The straight path is generated by spacing a number of steps in a straight line from point $x_1$ to $x_n$. So for 100 steps. $x = [(1,1),(2,2),(3,3),dots,(99,99),(100,100)]$.

=== Obstacles

Obstacles can defined as a new structure to the environment, this way it is very convenient check for collisions.
All obstacle is defined as a circles with a center-point, and a diameter.
