=== Learning rate schedulers
Another method used to optimize against noise is some kind of learning rate scheduler. Using a learning rate scheduler its much easier adapting the learning rate to the environment (and the task), opposed to fine tuning some very specific fixed learning rate. By using a scheduler, the learning rate instead changes over epochs, for a more dynamic training. There are many different scheduler great for different purposes. Each methods using a different kinds of learning rate decay $eta_(t+1) <- eta_t dot #[something]$
#figure(
